{"questionId":"26683","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the following directed network.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/1ba6342bdf54aab3dbf04848329fced9e1cc4b61.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the number of different walks of length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> that start and end at the same vertex.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>raising their matrix to a power of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">M</mi><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>17</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>9</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>17</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>10</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>13</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>6</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>8</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>18</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>11</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></m